title: SHEIN
text: It has almost everything you can think of with insane discounts. Some of the things I had ordered had been delivered broken (such as necklaces and bracelets) or they don’t work at all (such as electronics/tools.) Overall, everything came in perfect packaging, and came in the estimated time it showed.

title: An Honest Review
text:
I’ve bought things on SHEIN a few times, all though it did take a while for the things to come. I’ll estimate about a week or 2 for my packages to arrive. I was shown this app by my cousin and she loved shopping there. I’ve heard a few rumors about SHEIN using “child labor” but I’m not certain if it’s true. I’ve done research and I was reading different sources about SHEIN doing child labor, sometimes I was reading that SHEIN wasn’t doing child labor, therefore I was reading different information from different sources. 
Now the things I bought off SHEIN were just clothes and some of them were really nice, I’d say I kept the clothes for 2 years then I got rid of them. Some of the clothes were just horrible and I didn’t like how they turned out. I returned the clothes a couple of times and I was bummed out. 
In conclusion, I give SHEIN a 3 star because I’m not sure if SHEIN actually does child labor and I’m absolutely certain that SHEIN isn’t a great store. SHEIN might be hiding something and I don’t trust what it is.
